Justin Kauffman is the Founder and Managing Partner of Dominion Private Wealth, where he works with successful families and business owners to design, build, and steward wealth with clarity, discipline, and purpose, supported by a coordinated, team-based approach.
“Good planning prepares you for the future; great planning aligns it with what matters most.”
Justin earned a Bachelor of Science in Business Administration with an emphasis in Finance and a minor in Accounting from Adams State University in Colorado. While in school, he competed as a collegiate football and basketball player, experiences that reinforced the importance of preparation, accountability, and teamwork. He remains an avid sports enthusiast.

As a Certified Financial Planner™ (CFP®) and Certified Exit Planning Advisor® (CEPA®), Justin brings an integrated perspective spanning investment management, tax strategy, business advisory, and legacy planning. He serves as the lead advisor and strategic architect for each client relationship, while working alongside a carefully aligned team of professionals including tax, estate, and business planning specialists to ensure every recommendation is coordinated and intentional.

Justin founded Dominion Private Wealth on the conviction that meaningful financial planning requires more than isolated advice. The firm operates on a collaborative model, where investment strategy, tax planning, estate considerations, and business decisions are integrated into a single, cohesive framework. This team-based structure allows clients to benefit from deep expertise without fragmentation, while maintaining a clear point of leadership and accountability.

Raised in Alaska, Justin developed a strong sense of self-reliance, stewardship, and responsibility values that continue to shape his personal and professional philosophy. He now lives in Arizona with his wife and three young children, where faith, family, and community remain central to his life. Outside the office, he enjoys the outdoors, and building meaningful, long-term relationships. His mission is to help families steward wealth wisely, confidently, and in alignment with what matters most.
